.head 3 -  !
.head 3 +  Function: TableAnyRows
.head 4 -  Description: Determines if any table rows are on and or off and a count of how many.
.head 4 +  Returns
.head 5 -  Boolean:
.head 4 +  Parameters
.head 5 -  Window Handle: hWndTable
.head 5 -  Number: nRowFlagsOn
.head 5 -  Number: nRowFlagsOff
.head 5 -  Receive Number: nCount
.head 4 -  Static Variables
.head 4 +  Local variables
.head 5 -  Number: nRow
.head 5 -  Boolean: bFoundRow
.head 4 +  Actions
.head 5 -  Call OurWaitCursor( TRUE )
.head 5 -  Set bFoundRow = FALSE
.head 5 -  Set nCount = 0
.head 5 -  Set nRow = TBL_MinRow
.head 5 +  While SalTblFindNextRow( hWndTable, nRow, nRowFlagsOn, nRowFlagsOff )
.head 6 -  Set nCount = nCount + 1
.head 6 -  Set bFoundRow = TRUE
.head 5 -  Call OurWaitCursor( FALSE )
.head 5 -  Return bFoundRow
.head 3 +  Function: TableLoop
.head 4 -  Description: This function performs a loop thourgh table rows and for each row
a message is sent to the table for some action per row.  The lParam
of the message has the row position. nPAM_ROWACTION is a 
parameter which should have a message passed.  nFlagsOn and 
nFlagsOff are the Row Flag parameters as found the SalTblFindNexRow( ).
The sHeading is a heading which will appear on the meter dialog if more
than nTBL_cls_NumRowsToMeter constant ( set to 10 ) rows.  nDirection is either 
TBL_cls_LowToHi or TBL_cls_HiToLow and represent the order in which the table will be 
looped.  A TRUE must be returned to the nPAM_ROWACTION message,
if not the loop will terminate.
NOTE: If in the case that under nPAM_ROWACTION a row is deleted
with TBL_Adjust then the row count needs to be decremented or 
incremented so that normal loop continuation occurs.  To achieve this
the constant TBL_cls_RowDeleted must be returned to the nPAM_ROWACTION
message and this routine will adjust the row position variable 
accordingly.
NEW FEATURE AS OF 2/3/95: Use 
TBL_cls_LowToHiWithPositioning OR TBL_cls_HiToLowWithPositioning to have the
current processing row set the focus row and change the text color
to RED as its processing rows!
.head 4 +  Returns
.head 5 -  Boolean:
.head 4 +  Parameters
.head 5 -  Window Handle: hWndTable
.head 5 -  Window Handle: hWndRowAction
.head 5 -  Number: nPAM_ROWACTION
.head 5 -  Number: nMSG_wParam
.head 5 -  Number: nFlagsOn
.head 5 -  Number: nFlagsOff
.head 5 -  String: sHeading
.head 5 -  Number: nDirection
.head 4 -  Static Variables
.head 4 +  Local variables
.head 5 -  : Meter
.head 6 -  Class: clsMeterBar
.head 5 -  Number: nRow
.head 5 -  Number: nTotalRows
.head 5 -  Number: nActionReturn
.head 5 -  Number: nError
.head 5 -  Number: nLastRow
.head 5 -  Number: nOrgColor
.head 4 +  Actions
.head 5 +  If SalSendMsg( hWndTable, PAM_clsTBL_SETTBLLOOPTOTAL, nMSG_wParam, nPAM_ROWACTION )
.head 6 -  Call PopNumber( nTotalRows, TRUE )
.head 5 +  Else
.head 6 -  Call TableAnyRows( hWndTable, nFlagsOn, nFlagsOff, nTotalRows )
.head 5 -  !
.head 5 +  If nTotalRows > 0
.head 6 -  Call OurWaitCursor( TRUE )
.head 6 -  Set nError = FALSE
.head 6 +  If nTotalRows >= TBL_cls_NumRowsToMeter
.head 7 -  Call Meter.Setup( sHeading, nTotalRows )
.head 6 -  !
.head 6 +  ! If nDirection = TBL_cls_LowToHiWithPositioning OR nDirection = TBL_cls_HiToLowWithPositioning
.head 7 -    Set nOrgColor = SalColorGet( hWndTable, COLOR_IndexWindowText )
.head 6 -  !
.head 6 +  If nDirection = TBL_cls_LowToHi OR nDirection = TBL_cls_LowToHiWithPositioning
.head 7 -  Set nRow = TBL_MinRow
.head 7 -  Set nLastRow = TBL_MinRow
.head 7 +  While SalTblFindNextRow( hWndTable, nRow, nFlagsOn, nFlagsOff )
.head 8 -  Call SalTblFetchRow( hWndTable, nRow )
.head 8 -  !
.head 8 +  If nDirection = TBL_cls_LowToHiWithPositioning
.head 9 +  If nLastRow = TBL_MinRow
.head 10 -  Set nOrgColor = SalColorGet( hWndTable, COLOR_IndexWindowText )
.head 9 +  Else
.head 10 -  Call SalTblFetchRow( hWndTable, nLastRow )
.head 10 -  Call SalSendMsgToChildren( hWndTable, PAM_clsTBL_SETCOLUMNCOLOR, 0, nOrgColor )
.head 10 -  Call SalTblFetchRow( hWndTable, nRow )
.head 9 -  ! Call SalTblSetFocusRow( hWndTable, nRow )
.head 9 -  Call SalSendMsgToChildren( hWndTable, PAM_clsTBL_SETCOLUMNCOLOR, 0, COLOR_Red )
.head 8 -  !
.head 8 -  Call Meter.Increment( 1 )
.head 8 -  Set nActionReturn = SalSendMsg( hWndRowAction, nPAM_ROWACTION, nMSG_wParam, nRow )
.head 8 +  If nActionReturn = FALSE
.head 9 -  Set nError = TRUE
.head 9 -  Break
.head 8 +  Else If nActionReturn = TBL_cls_RowDeleted
.head 9 -  Set nRow = nRow - 1
.head 8 -  !
.head 8 -  Set nLastRow = nRow
.head 7 +  If nDirection = TBL_cls_LowToHiWithPositioning
.head 8 -  Call SalSendMsgToChildren( hWndTable, PAM_clsTBL_SETCOLUMNCOLOR, 0, nOrgColor )
.head 6 +  Else
.head 7 -  Set nRow = TableLocateLastRow( hWndTable, nFlagsOn, nFlagsOff ) + 1
.head 7 -  Set nLastRow = nRow
