.head 5 +    Function: ForgetChanges
.head 6 -    Description: Prompts the user that they forgot to save their changes,
and asks if they want the CHANCE to save them.
If they click YES (they want to save their changes) this 
functions returns FALSE because we do not want to 
forget the changes.  Else it returns TRUE indicating
stuff the changes.
.head 6 +    Returns 
.head 7 -    Boolean: 
.head 6 -    Parameters 
.head 6 -    Static Variables 
.head 6 -    Local variables 
.head 6 +    Actions 
.head 7 +    If IDYES = SalMessageBox( 'Your current changes have not been saved.
Would you like the chance to save them to the database?', 'Warning',
MB_YesNo )
.head 8 -    Call SalMessageBox( 'Please SAVE / ADD your changes!', 'NOTE', MB_Ok )
.head 8 -    Return FALSE
.head 7 +    Else 
.head 8 -    Return TRUE
